data.enText: to join pieces of metal together by heating their edges and pressing them together

data.chText: 这辆汽车焊上了一块新挡泥板。
data.enText: The car has had a new wing welded on.

data.chText: 这件雕塑所有的部件都必须焊接在一起。
data.enText: All the parts of the sculpture have to be welded together.

data.chText: 使紧密结合；使连成整体
data.enText: to unite people or things into a strong and effective group

data.chText: 他们把一群未经训练的新兵组织成了一支有战斗力的部队。
data.enText: They had welded a bunch of untrained recruits into an efficient fighting force.

data.chText: 这场危机促使整个党紧密地团结在一起。
data.enText: The crisis helped to weld the party together.

tr: a metal joint formed by softening with heat and fusing or hammering together
European mignonette cultivated as a source of yellow dye

example: Her gratitude welded her to him

value.def: To weld one piece of metal to another means to join them by heating the edges and putting them together so that they cool and harden into one piece.

example.ex: It's possible to weld stainless steel to ordinary steel...
example.tran: 不锈钢是有可能和普通钢焊接在一起的。

example.ex: They will also be used on factory floors to weld things together...
example.tran: 它们也可用于工厂车间，用来焊接物体。

example.ex: Where did you learn to weld?
example.tran: 你在哪儿学会的焊接技术？

example.ex: All the welding had been done from inside the car...
example.tran: 所有的焊接都在车内完成。

value.def: A weld is a join where two pieces of metal have been welded together.
If you weld people together, you join them together to form a united organization.

example.ex: She has both the authority and the personality to weld the party together...
example.tran: 团结全党所需的权威和个人魅力她两者兼具。

example.ex: The miracle was that Rose had welded them into a team.
example.tran: 令人称叹的是罗斯把他们打造成了一个团队。

trans: 焊接关节；焊接接头；焊缝
焊缝渗透深度；熔深；焊透深度；焊接熔深
